Growler Fill on the Brewery tour

One of the better porters I have had in a while. Chocolate start and finish. Dark brown pour with a minimal light brown head. Good beer. Wish it was local to my area!

Draft @ Rattle N HUM NYC

Good Witbier that was the last beer of the night for me. Pours a yellow color with a nice head that doesnt last long. IMO another good session beer!

Draft @ Rattle N Hum

Best beer I had all night! Dark brown, almost black pour with a light brown head that didnt last long. Smokey and Nutty first sip and lasted through the entire pint! Would have this beer again in a heartbeat!

Draft @ Rattle N Hum NYC

Another beer that I like very much from Stone Brewing Co. I wish there brewhouse was around the corner from me. No such luck though. Poured an amber color with a foamy ivory head. Citrus and malt punch in the first sip that I loved coming back for. Would definitely drink again!

Draft @ Rattle N Hum NYC..

Great Session Beer! I felt like I can drink this beer into the wee hours of the night. Oh wait I did that! Very good smelling beer, with hints of orange and lemon on the first sip. A cloudy orange pour. Would definitely drink again!

Serving: Bottle Rated 8/1/2010 

Decent Pilsner. My first try of a Troegs brew. Pours a light yellow with average head. To be honest it tasted like everyother pilsner I have ever had. Nothng jumped out at me to where I would need to have this beer again. Just decent.

Serving: Bottle Rated 8/1/2010 First LeftHand Brewing Company beer for me. Pours a light amber color with little to no head. Fruity smell and finish. Decent beer. Wouldnt go out of my way to have it again.
Draft @ The Pony Bar :: Not a fan of this one. Little to no aroma, tasted like the bottom of the keg. Very flat in the glass as well. One and done
Draft @ The Pony Bar 7/23/2010 Cloudy Dark Yellow pour with minimum head, foam was an off white and didnt last very long. Fruity aroma with bitter taste at the end. Enjoyed it.

Draft / Growler..Saw this on tap at a craft beer liquor store. My best friend swears by this beer and I figured I had to try it. Love the way this beer pours. Sweet smell, looks like wine and guinness combined. Fruity start to a Chocolate fade finish. Love this beer. 7/22/2010
One of my favorite beers of the moment. Love the Maltiness and hoppiness of this one. Cant wait to try all of the other beers Rogue has to offer. Rated 7/22/2010

First taste of a Cricket Hill Brewing Company Beer. Tastes and Smells like a Summer beer, hence the name I guess. Looks like a darker version of a Blue Moon, but this tastes so much better. Rated 7/22/2010
beer_name: Cricket Hill Jersey Summer Breakfast Ale
